verbose_text: From the growth curves, it could be inferred that it was not because of Nisin inhibiting the growth of NZ3900 / pNZ8110-hspA as inhibitory but because HspA had not been induced to be expressed effectively in 10 ng/mL Nisin group, while, in higher concentrations of Nisin group, a small amount of exogenous expression of HspA inhibited the growth of NZ3900 / pNZ8110-hspA itself.
evidence: HspA had not been induced to be expressed effectively in 10 ng/mL Nisin group
